## 4. GEO — Generative Engine Optimization

This is what makes this system different. GEO ensures your content is not just ranked by Google but cited by AI answer engines (ChatGPT, Perplexity, Gemini, Google AI Overviews).

### Why GEO Matters

- AI-referred website sessions grew 527% in H1 2025.
- 58% of users have replaced traditional search with AI tools.
- LLMs cite only 2–7 domains per response. If you are not one of them, you do not exist in AI search.
- 89% of B2B buyers use generative AI in their purchasing journey.

### GEO Rules

**4.1 Direct Answer Formatting**
The first 40–60 words of every key section must directly answer the implied question. AI models prioritise immediate, extractable answers. Do not bury the answer under preamble.

**4.2 Statistical Density**
Include a relevant statistic, data point, or quantified claim every 150–200 words. AI engines favour fact-dense content over opinion.

**4.3 Source Citation Within Content**
Reference credible sources (studies, industry reports, named experts) in the body text. AI engines treat content with citations as more trustworthy and are more likely to cite it in return.

**4.4 Entity Clarity**
Every entity (person, brand, product, concept) must be introduced with enough context for an AI model to understand what it is and why it is relevant. No ambiguous references.

**4.5 Conversational Query Mapping**
AI search queries average 23 words vs 4 words on Google. Structure content to answer natural language questions, not just short-tail keywords.

**4.6 FAQ Sections for AI Extraction**
Every piece of content must include a clearly structured FAQ section with 4–6 questions. Use the exact question as the heading. Provide concise, direct answers. This is the single most extractable format for AI citation.

**4.7 Schema Markup Recommendations**
For every piece of content, recommend appropriate schema types:
- **Article** — Blog posts, guides, long-form content
- **FAQPage** — Pages with Q&A sections (restricted to gov/health as of Aug 2023)
- **Product** — Product pages with pricing/reviews
- **LocalBusiness** — Location-based service pages
- **Person** — Author pages, about pages (builds E-E-A-T)
- **VideoObject** — Video content pages
- **SoftwareApplication** — SaaS/app pages

Include specific JSON-LD structure the developer can implement.

**4.8 Content Modularity**
Write in modular, self-contained sections. Each H2 section should be independently extractable by an AI engine. Avoid cross-references that require reading the full article to understand a single section.

