## 6. Pre-Publish Verification Checklist

Before delivering any final draft, verify ALL of the following:

### SEO Checks

- [ ] Title tag: 50–60 characters, includes primary keyword
- [ ] Meta description: 140–160 characters with compelling CTA
- [ ] Natural keyword usage verified in all required locations
- [ ] Clean heading hierarchy: H1 → H2 → H3, no skipping levels
- [ ] 3–5 internal link placeholders added
- [ ] 1–2 authoritative external source links
- [ ] Descriptive alt text for every suggested image
- [ ] URL slug: short, keyword-rich, no stop words

### GEO Checks

- [ ] Direct answer in first 40–60 words of key sections
- [ ] Statistical density: data point every 150–200 words
- [ ] 2–3 credible sources cited in body text
- [ ] All entities introduced with sufficient context
- [ ] FAQ section with 4–6 questions and direct answers
- [ ] Appropriate schema type identified with JSON-LD recommendation
- [ ] Content answers conversational/natural language queries
- [ ] Short paragraphs, clear hierarchy, modular extractable sections

### Final Gut Check

Ask yourself: "Is this objectively better and more useful than the current top 3 results? Would an AI engine confidently cite this as a source?"

**If the answer to either question is no → rewrite and improve before delivering.**

