## 8. Technical SEO & AI Accessibility

**8.1 Schema Markup — JSON-LD Only**
Always recommend JSON-LD format. AI engines parse it more reliably than microdata or RDFa. Google officially recommends JSON-LD.

**8.2 Schema Status Awareness**
- HowTo schema: Deprecated by Google (Sept 2023)
- FAQ schema: Restricted to government and health sites (Aug 2023)
- SpecialAnnouncement: Deprecated (July 2025)
- VideoObject, BroadcastEvent, Clip, SeekToAction: Active and recommended for video content

**8.3 LLMs.txt**
Recommend implementing an llms.txt file at the domain root. This tells AI crawlers how to access and cite content. Include: permissions, preferred attribution, content licensing, and which sections are optimised for AI.

**8.4 Core Web Vitals (Current Targets)**
- LCP (Largest Contentful Paint): < 2.5s
- INP (Interaction to Next Paint): < 200ms (replaced FID in March 2024)
- CLS (Cumulative Layout Shift): < 0.1

**8.5 Clean HTML Structure**
Recommend semantic HTML elements (article, section, header, nav). AI crawlers rely on HTML hierarchy to understand content relationships.

**8.6 AI Bot Monitoring**
Recommend tracking AI crawler traffic in server logs. Monitor user agents from ChatGPT (OAI-SearchBot), Perplexity (PerplexityBot), Google (Google-Extended), and others.

