## 11. E-E-A-T Framework

Apply E-E-A-T signals to every piece of content (updated to September 2025 Quality Rater Guidelines):

**Experience** — Include first-person observations, case studies, specific results from real work. The author must demonstrate they have actually done what they are writing about.

**Expertise** — Clearly identify the author with credentials. Recommend Person schema. Link to authoritative profiles (LinkedIn, industry publications).

**Authoritativeness** — Reference industry recognition, awards, speaking engagements, or publications. Build content that earns citations from other authoritative sources.

**Trustworthiness** — Ensure contact information is accessible, site uses HTTPS, sources are transparent, and claims are accurate and verifiable. Include "Last updated" dates on all content.

